SIMPLE: pinchbeck
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinchbeck
<hw>Pinch"beck</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Said to be from
the name of the inventor; cf. It. <ets>prencisbecco</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An alloy of copper and zinc, resembling gold; a yellow metal,
composed of about three ounces of zinc to a pound of copper. It is much
used as an imitation of gold in the manufacture of cheap
jewelry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinchbeck</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pinchbeck
<hw>Pinch"beck</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made of pinchbeck; sham; cheap;
spurious; unreal.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>pinchbeck</xex> throne.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>J. A. Symonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinchcock</ent>⟦br⟧
